author: Adam Edelman
description: Iowa Democrats haven't had much to cheer in recent years.
title: Special election win excites Iowa Democrats, but Republicans remain confident

description: CDC Director Susan Monarez is leaving the agency, just weeks after taking the position. This comes as three other top CDC officials have resigned. NBC News' Berkeley Lovelace Jr. explains the latest changes.
title: CDC director leaves agency just weeks into job

author: Erika Edwards
description: The director of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention and several top officials are departing in a massive shakeup at the embattled agency.
title: CDC director pushed out, flood of top resignations follow

author: Kimmy Yam
description: A group of Israeli citizens filed a legal document this week in support of Mohsen Mahdawi, a Palestinian student at Columbia University who was taken into custody during his naturalization interview in April.
title: More than two dozen Israeli citizens file court document backing Columbia student Mohsen Mahdawi

author: Tim Stelloh
description: A Southern California man accused of killing his wife and fleeing to Peru with their children surrendered Wednesday to authorities in the South American country, authorities said
title: Fugitive accused of killing wife who was found dead in California forest surrenders in Peru

author: The Politics Desk
description: Almost two weeks after the Alaska summit between Trump and Putin, there’s still no end in sight to the war in Ukraine.
title: Post-Alaska summit, there's still no end in sight to the war in Ukraine: From the Politics Desk

author: Kevin Collier
description: Three private Chinese companies helped China carry out one of the boldest hacking operations to date, including snooping on text messages from the Kamala Harris and Donald Trump campaigns in 2021, according to a coalition of U.S. agencies and 12 allied governments
title: China used three private companies to hack global telecoms, U.S. says

author: Daniel Arkin
description: MINNEAPOLIS — Mike Garrity was walking home from the gym Wednesday morning when he heard a series of loud noises that he initially thought were coming from a nail gun at a construction site
title: Minneapolis shooting witnesses and nearby residents describe harrowing scenes

description: Minneapolis Police Chief Brian O'Hara said the gunman in the deadly school church shooting acted alone and had timed a manifesto to be released on YouTube that included “disturbing writings.” The manifesto has been taken down and remains under active review.
title: Minneapolis shooter had manifesto timed to post on YouTube, officials say

author: Rebecca Shabad
description: D.C. Mayor Muriel Bowser said Trump's surge of federal authorities lowered crime but the presence of ICE agents and the National Guard isn't working.
title: Mayor Muriel Bowser says Trump's surge of federal law enforcement has lowered crime in D.C.

description: Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz spoke to reporters after two children were killed and 17 were injured in a mass shooting of Catholic school students at a Minneapolis church. "Minnesotans will not step away. We'll stand with this community," Walz said.
title: Gov. Walz 'will stand with this community' after shooting

author: Rebecca Cohen
description: The suspect who opened fire in Minneapolis on a Catholic school during Mass has been identified by officials as a person in their early 20s who left behind videos online with writings that referenced suicide.
title: What we know about the gunman in the Minneapolis Catholic school shooting

description: Mayor Muriel Bowser said that the presence of more federal law enforcement on the streets of Washington, D.C., has helped lower crime, but having masked ICE agents and National Guard members from other states in communities "has not worked."
title: Bowser: Crime in D.C. has fallen but more ICE and National Guard 'has not worked'

description: Weston Halsne, 10, describes hiding under the pews of Annunciation Church in Minneapolis as a gunman fired through the windows into the building. Weston said his friend "got hit" while laying on top of him.
title: 10-year-old says friend was shot laying on top of him

description: Robin Westman was identified as the suspected shooter who opened fire at the Annunciation Catholic School in Minneapolis. At least two children are dead and 17 others were injured during the incident.
title: Suspected Minneapolis church shooter identified as Robin Westman

author: Laura Strickler
description: WASHINGTON — At least 21 Federal Emergency Management Agency employees have been put on administrative leave after they signed an open letter criticizing the Trump administration's disaster preparedness and response capabilities, the founder of the organization behind the letter confirmed to NBC News.
title: FEMA employees placed on leave after criticizing the Trump administration in open letter

author: Berkeley Lovelace Jr.
description: The Food and Drug Administration approved the next round of Covid shots for the fall — but only for a smaller, high-risk group of people, Health and Human Services Secretary Robert F. Kennedy Jr.
title: FDA approves fall Covid shots, but with new restrictions

author: Deon J. Hampton
description: The family of a 4-year-old Oregon boy who suffered severe brain damage after being anesthetized by his dentist has filed a $22 million civil suit against the doctor.
title: Family of 4-year-old with brain damage files a $22 million lawsuit against dentist

author: Brennan Leach
description: Sen. Susan Collins, R-Maine, was heckled and drowned out by demonstrators at a ribbon-cutting ceremony in her home state Tuesday, the latest in a series of confrontations between protesters and members of Congress.
title: Sen. Susan Collins drowned out by protesters at Maine ribbon-cutting event

description: NBC News’ Tom Winter reports on how police believe the suspect carried out a shooting at Annunciation Catholic School in Minneapolis while Mass was taking place. Police say the suspect, who appeared to have died from a self-inflicted gunshot wound, had no significant criminal history.
title: What’s known so far about suspect in Minneapolis church mass shooting

author: David K. Li
description: The Northern Virginia man, accused of murdering his wife, tapped into a BDSM fetish dating website to lure a patsy who'd play an unwitting role in getting his spouse "out of the picture,” the suspect's au pair lover and co-defendant said.
title: Wife's murder connected to elaborate sex fetish-based plot, according to au pair

author: Ryan J. Reilly
description: WASHINGTON — You could get a grand jury to indict a ham sandwich, the saying goes, but, in Washington, a federal grand jury just declined to indict a man for throwing a salami sub
title: Grand jury declines to indict man who threw a sandwich at federal officer in D.C.

author: The Associated Press
description: A conservative election researcher who pushed faulty findings about the 2020 election has been appointed to an election integrity role at the U.S.
title: Researcher who has distorted voter data appointed to DHS election integrity role

author: Reuters
description: OROZMANI, Georgia — Archaeologists in Georgia have unearthed a 1.8-million-year-old jawbone belonging to an early species of human that they say will shed light on some of the earliest prehistoric human settlements on the Eurasian continent
title: Archaeologists in Georgia unearth 1.8-million-year-old human jawbone

author: Reuters
description: South Korea passed a bill on Wednesday to ban the use of mobile phones and other digital devices in school classrooms nationwide, as concern grows about the impact of heavy social media use among the young.
title: South Korea to ban mobile phones in school classrooms

author: Minyvonne Burke
description: The California parents accused of falsely claiming that their 7-month-old son was kidnapped from a store parking lot were charged Tuesday with murder.
title: Parents accused of fake kidnapping story are charged with murder as search for son continues

author: Henry Austin
description: President Donald Trump was set to chair a meeting Wednesday about the future of Gaza, as Israel faced mounting global outcry over strikes on a hospital that killed 20 people, including journalists and medics.
title: Israel faces new pressure over hospital strikes as Trump chairs Gaza meeting

author: Megan Lebowitz
description: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration is planning to take over the management of D.C.’s Union Station, the travel hub for Amtrak and the city’s metro lines, the Transportation Department announced Wednesday morning.
title: Transportation Department announces plans to take over D.C.'s Union Station

author: Kevin Collier
description: A hacker has exploited a leading artificial intelligence chatbot to conduct the most comprehensive and lucrative AI cybercriminal operation known to date, using it to do everything from find targets to write ransom notes
title: A hacker used AI to automate an 'unprecedented' cybercrime spree, Anthropic says

author: Rebecca Cohen
description: It was the "proposal heard 'round the world," and Jason Kelce is taking a moment to loudly celebrate his brother, Travis Kelce, and his soon-to-be sister-in-law, Taylor Swift.
title: Jason Kelce celebrates Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce's 'proposal heard 'round the world'

author: Melissa Chan
description: A Wisconsin high school dean’s recent arrest on multiple charges of sex crimes against children has triggered an uproar among parents who say school leaders dismissed warning signs and failed to alert authorities to at least one credible claim.
title: A dean was charged with sex crimes against children. Parents say school failures enabled him.

description: It's a love story! Music super star Taylor Swift and NFL star Travis Kelce announced their engagement on Instagram on Tuesday with the caption reading, “Your English teacher and your gym teacher are getting married.” Now, Kelce’s dad is speaking out revealing he actually popped the question about two weeks prior to the announcement in a garden in Lee’s Summit, Missouri. NBC’s Emilie Ikeda reports for TODAY.
title: Travis Kelce’s Dad Speaks Out Following Taylor Swift Engagement

author: Daryna Mayer
description: KYIV, Ukraine — Russian troops have for the first time entered a key Ukrainian region, Kyiv's military said Wednesday, as President Donald Trump’s special envoy offered new details on the Kremlin's demands and stressed that the U.S. peace push remained on track
title: Russian troops enter key Ukrainian region as Trump envoy says talks are ongoing

description: President Donald Trump’s battle with the Federal Reserve is heating up after his abrupt move to fire Lisa Cook, a member of the Fed’s Board of Governors. Cook’s lawyer is now vowing to sue the Trump administration to challenge her removal which he calls an “illegal action.” It comes as Trump indicated in a cabinet meeting Tuesday that he wants to fill the board with allies. "We'll have a majority very shortly," he said. NBC’s Peter Alexander reports for TODAY from the White House.
title: Trump Signals He Wants to Fill Federal Reserve Board With Allies

author: Curtis Bunn
description: Hurricane Katrina devastated families and communities, but for some, the most memorable part is how many strangers showed up to lend a hand.
title: Hurricane Katrina survivors remember the acts of compassion that saved them 20 years ago

author: Maya Huter
description: Some back-to-school prices are higher, some are lower, and others have stayed put since last year.
title: Back-to-school prices are a mixed bag this year

author: Natasha Korecki
description: MINNEAPOLIS — Democrats are already looking to assemble their early-state presidential nominating calendar for 2028, with the party announcing Tuesday that it would kick off the process in September.
title: Democrats prepare to set their 2028 presidential nominating calendar

author: Patrick Smith
description: A time capsule placed inside a wall at a London children's hospital by Diana, Princess of Wales been opened for the first time in almost 35 years, revealing a treasure trove of 1990s memorabilia.
title: Time capsule sealed by Princess Diana is revealed decades later

author: Sahil Kapur
description: WASHINGTON — The House Freedom Caucus faces an existential moment with some of its most prominent members eyeing the exits for new jobs in the 2026 election, calling into question the future of the band of far-right rebels.Rep.
title: Hard-right Freedom Caucus could be gutted as key members run for new jobs in 2026

author: Mithil Aggarwal
description: President Donald Trump's promised 50% tariffs on India took effect on Wednesday, as the U.S. risks blowing up a relationship considered crucial in its effort to counter the rise of China
title: Trump's tariffs on India rise to 50% in punishment for buying Russian oil

author: Dennis Romero
description: Legal proceedings for four Army soldiers charged in connection with the sexual assault of a college student in an Army barracks began this month, a spokesperson for the military branch said
title: 4 Army soldiers charged in connection with on-base sexual assault of college student who's now an officer

author: Zoë Richards
description: Catelin Drey's win gives her party an additional seat, bringing the number of Democrats serving in the upper chamber to 17 and breaking Republicans' two-thirds supermajority.
title: Democrats break GOP supermajority in Iowa Senate by flipping Republican seat in special election

author: David Rohde
description: A top Senate Democrat said new FBI deputy director Andrew Bailey used his power as Missouri’s attorney general to aid President Trump politically.
title: New FBI deputy director will help Trump 'weaponize' bureau, top Democrat says

author: Alicia Victoria Lozano
description: A Southern California border agent charged with assaulting a Long Beach police officer outside a restaurant and resisting arrest last month died just two days after his most recent court appearance
title: Border agent charged with assaulting police officer dies days after court appearance
